tput `anyedge_dut` will not have changed yet (as it is synchronous), but the testbench checks it. This leads to a mismatch because the testbench is sampling the outputs at a time (negedge) when the synchronous DUT hasn't updated to reflect the new input yet.\n7. Therefore, the testbench is flawed because its verification mechanism (the `always` block and the stimulus generation) does not respect the synchronous nature of the design, leading to false mismatches on the negative edges.",
